data.name: checkUseGuardianAerialScreenshotsFolder.Text
data.value: Save Ruins aerial screenshots into site-type specific sub-folders. Eg: 'Aerial alpha', 'Aerial beta' or 'Aerial gamma' Screenshots need to be within 50m of site origin, with an altitude between 500m and 2000m.

data.name: linkAboutOne.Text
data.value:
SrvSurvey is an independent third-party application for use with Elite Dangerous.
It provides on-screen assistance when a player is near a planet in the SRV, on foot or in ships. It had 3 main functions: - Organic scans: Track the location of organic scans and the distance required for the next scan. - Ground target tracking: Aiming guidance towards latitude/longitude co-ordinates. - Guardian sites: Track visited areas and the locations of items within Guardian ruins and structures.
This tool was inspired by the work of the Guardian Science Corps and aims to help anyone exploring the mysteries of the Guardians.
I'd like to give special thanks to V Clara and Running Wild for their inspiration and help with Ruins and Structures. To Running Wild (again) and LilacLight for their excellent map backgrounds. To Seventh_Circle for his original Ruins background maps, Arras for the genus ring graphics, to EvilHorse for her data used to make species predictions, to MattG for his exploration reward formula, CMDR Just for the Srv Survey icon and many others at Canonn.
Finally to Brammmers for his dedication and patience whilst we ironed out the bugs in bio-scanning features.
